#: buildVars.py:14
msgid "freeRadio"
msgstr "freeRadio"

#: buildVars.py:18
msgid ""
"FreeRadio is an internet radio add-on for NVDA that provides seamless access "
"to thousands of stations via the Radio Browser open directory. It features a "
"fully accessible station browser with search, country filter, favourites "
"management, and per-station audio profiles. Playback is handled by a "
"prioritised backend chain (BASS, VLC, PotPlayer, Windows Media Player) with "
"support for volume control, audio effects, output device selection, and "
"simultaneous audio mirroring to a second device. Additional features include "
"instant and scheduled recording, sleep and alarm timers, automatic ICY "
"metadata announcements, Shazam-based music recognition, and a liked-songs "
"log. All controls and shortcuts are designed for NVDA accessibility."
msgstr ""
"FreeRadio é um complemento de rádio na Internet para o NVDA que fornece "
"acesso contínuo a milhares de estações através do diretório aberto do Radio "
"Browser. Possui um navegador de estação totalmente acessível com pesquisa, "
"filtro de país, gerenciamento de favoritos e perfis de áudio por estação. A "
"reprodução é feita por uma cadeia de back-end priorizada (BASS, VLC, "
"PotPlayer, Windows Media Player) com suporte para controle de volume, "
"efeitos de áudio, seleção de dispositivo de saída e espelhamento de áudio "
"simultâneo para um segundo dispositivo. Recursos adicionais incluem gravação "
"instantânea e programada, temporizadores de suspensão e alarme, anúncios "
"automáticos de metadados ICY, reconhecimento de música baseado em Shazam e "
"um registro de músicas favoritas. Todos os controles e atalhos são "
"projetados para acessibilidade do NVDA."

#: buildVars.py:25
msgid ""
"\n"
"- Change reorder favorite key to comma because * doesn't work for many "
"keyboard layout.\n"
"**Fixed**\n"
"- `ctrl+win+r` and other hotkeys silently failing to reopen the station "
"browser dialog after it had been hidden at least once.\n"
"\n"
"**Root cause:** NVDA maintains an internal popup counter that is incremented "
"by `prePopup()` and decremented by `postPopup()`. `prePopup()` was called "
"once when the dialog was first created, but none of the code paths that hide "
"the dialog (`_on_close_btn`, `_on_window_close`, ESC key, Enter on Close "
"button, Alt+K, `_force_destroy`) ever called `postPopup()`. The counter "
"therefore grew by one on every open/hide cycle and never decreased. After "
"enough cycles NVDA interpreted the accumulated count as \"another popup is "
"already open\" and silently blocked subsequent `Show()` calls, causing the "
"dialog to appear completely unresponsive to all hotkeys with no error "
"logged.\n"
"\n"
"**Fix:** Added `gui.mainFrame.postPopup()` after every `self.Hide()` and "
"`self.Destroy()` call in `radioDialog.py`. Added a matching "
"`gui.mainFrame.prePopup()` in `_open_dialog()` (`__init__.py`) for the re-"
"show path, so each `prePopup` is correctly paired with a `postPopup` for the "
"full lifetime of the dialog.\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"- A tecla de atalho para reordenar favoritos foi alterada para vírgula "
"(`,`), pois o `*` não funciona em muitos layouts de teclado.\n"
"**Corrigido**\n"
"- `ctrl+win+r` e outros atalhos falhando silenciosamente ao tentar reabrir o "
"diálogo do navegador de estações após ele ter sido ocultado pelo menos uma "
"vez.\n"
"**Causa raiz:** O NVDA mantém um contador interno de popups que é "
"incrementado por `prePopup()` e decrementado por `postPopup()`. O "
"`prePopup()` era chamado uma vez quando o diálogo era criado pela primeira "
"vez, mas nenhum dos caminhos de código que ocultam o diálogo "
"(`_on_close_btn`, `_on_window_close`, tecla ESC, Enter no botão Fechar, "
"Alt+K, `_force_destroy`) jamais chamava `postPopup()`. O contador, portanto, "
"aumentava em um a cada ciclo de abertura/ocultação e nunca diminuía. Após "
"ciclos suficientes, o NVDA interpretava a contagem acumulada como \"outro "
"popup já está aberto\" e bloqueava silenciosamente as chamadas subsequentes "
"de `Show()`, fazendo com que o diálogo parecesse completamente sem resposta "
"a todos os atalhos, sem nenhum erro registrado.\n"
"**Correção:** Adicionado `gui.mainFrame.postPopup()` após cada chamada de "
"`self.Hide()` e `self.Destroy()` em `radioDialog.py`. Adicionado um "
"`gui.mainFrame.prePopup()` correspondente em `_open_dialog()` "
"(`__init__.py`) para o caminho de reexibição, de modo que cada `prePopup` "
"seja corretamente emparelhado com um `postPopup` durante todo o ciclo de "
"vida do diálogo.\n"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\n"
#~ "**Focus management after item removal**\n"
#~ "- Favorites list: after deleting a station, focus and selection "
#~ "automatically move to the next item in the list. If the deleted station "
#~ "was the last one, focus moves to the previous item. If the list becomes "
#~ "empty, focus moves to the Play button.\n"
#~ "- Liked Songs list: same behaviour — after removing a song, focus stays "
#~ "on the next item, or moves to the Refresh button if the list is empty.\n"
#~ "**Delete key shortcut**\n"
#~ "- Pressing `Delete` while a station is selected in the Favorites list now "
#~ "triggers the Delete Station button (equivalent to clicking it), provided "
#~ "the button is enabled.\n"
#~ "- Pressing `Delete` while a song is selected in the Liked Songs list now "
#~ "triggers the Remove button, provided the button is enabled.\n"
#~ "- In both cases the key has no effect when no valid item is selected or "
#~ "the corresponding button is disabled.\n"
#~ "- Added a new \"Mute notifications\" checkbox to FreeRadio settings "
#~ "(unchecked by default).\n"
#~ "- When enabled, NVDA no longer announces station changes, playback state "
#~ "changes (play, pause, stop), or recording events (started, stopped, "
#~ "finished).\n"
#~ "- Error messages, favourites feedback, music recognition results, and "
#~ "update notifications are intentionally unaffected.\n"
#~ "- Added an unassigned script_toggleMuteNotifications input gesture that "
#~ "toggles the setting on the fly. Assign a key combination via NVDA's Input "
#~ "Gestures dialog under the FreeRadio category.\n"
#~ "- Two module-level helpers (_notify, _notify_on_demand) centralise the "
#~ "mute check, keeping call sites clean.\n"
#~ "**Changed: Search now filters by selected country automatically**\n"
#~ "- Search queries are now scoped to the selected country. When a country "
#~ "is chosen in the combo box, results are fetched from the API already "
#~ "filtered by that country rather than searching globally and filtering "
#~ "locally afterward.\n"
#~ "- The Search button has been removed. Results update automatically as you "
#~ "type (debounced, 500 ms delay), so a manual trigger is no longer needed.\n"
#~ "- Removed the Enter key and Alt+A shortcuts that previously triggered a "
#~ "manual search.\n"
#~ "- The search status message has been shortened. It now reads `\"query\": "
#~ "N in Country` instead of the previous `Search \"query\": N results (N in "
#~ "Country)`.\n"
#~ "- The key used for reordering favorites was changed from X to * (star).\n"
